%N A087170 Expansion of (1 + 4*x)/(1 + 7*x + 16*x^2).
%C A087170 For positive n, a(n) equals 4^n times the permanent of the (2n) X (2n) matrix with 1/2's along the main diagonal, and i's along the superdiagonal and the subdiagonal (where i is the imaginary unit). - _John M. Campbell_, Jul 08 2011
%H A087170 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (-7,-16).
%F A087170 G.f.: (1 + 4*x)/(1 + 7*x + 16*x^2).
%F A087170 a(n) = -7*a(n-1) - 16*a(n-2), a(0)=1, a(1)=-3.
%F A087170 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(n+k,2*k)*(-4)^(n-k).
